INSERT INTO exercises(id, title, description, is_custom, needs_equipment) VALUES
(1, 'Reverse Snow Angel', 'The Reverse Snow Angel is a dynamic bodyweight exercise that engages various muscle groups. Similar to the traditional snow angel motion, this exercise involves lying face down and moving your arms and legs in a coordinated, reverse motion. It targets the back, shoulders, and glutes, promoting strength, flexibility, and improved posture. The Reverse Snow Angel is a challenging yet rewarding workout that can be incorporated into your fitness routine for a full-body toning experience.', false, false),
(2, 'Side Bends', 'Side Bends are a simple yet effective exercise designed to target the obliques and strengthen the core. In this movement, you stand upright and gently lean to one side, engaging the muscles along the waistline. The exercise helps improve lateral flexibility, tones the sides of the torso, and contributes to a more sculpted midsection. Incorporating Side Bends into your fitness routine can enhance your overall core stability and promote a balanced, well-defined waistline.', false, false),
(3, 'Superman Elbow to Knee Touch', 'The Superman Elbow to Knee Touch exercise is a dynamic core workout that combines elements of the Superman and knee-to-elbow crunches. Starting in a prone position, you lift your arms and legs off the ground (mimicking Superman flying) and then bring the opposite elbow to knee in a controlled, twisting motion. This exercise effectively engages the abdominal muscles, particularly the obliques, enhancing core strength and promoting stability. The Superman Elbow to Knee Touch is an excellent choice for those seeking a challenging yet rewarding move to target both the front and sides of the core for a more comprehensive abdominal workout.', false, false),

(4, 'Diamond Push Ups', 'Diamond Push-Ups are a bodyweight exercise that targets the chest, triceps, and shoulders with a focus on the inner chest muscles. In this variation of the classic push-up, your hands are positioned close together under your chest, forming a diamond shape with your thumbs and index fingers. As you lower and raise your body, the emphasis shifts to the triceps and inner pectoral muscles. Diamond Push-Ups are an effective way to enhance upper body strength, build muscle definition, and provide a challenging alternative to traditional push-ups. They are particularly beneficial for those looking to intensify their chest and triceps workouts.', false, false),
(5, 'Tricep Dips', 'Tricep Dips are a powerful bodyweight exercise targeting the triceps, shoulders, and chest. To perform this exercise, you position your hands on a stable surface behind you, fingers pointing forward, and lower your body by bending your elbows. The movement effectively engages the triceps as you push your body back up to the starting position. Tricep Dips are a versatile exercise that can be done using parallel bars, a bench, or even the edge of a sturdy chair. They are ideal for building upper body strength, toning the arms, and improving overall arm definition. Incorporate Tricep Dips into your workout routine for a targeted and efficient arm-strengthening exercise.', false, false),
(6, 'Reverse Push-Ups', 'Reverse Push-Ups is similar to traditional pushups, but with a reverse palms or fists position. This exercise improves strength and definition in the upper body, particularly the biceps, while also engaging shoulders. Incorporating Reverse Push-Ups into your routine can help promote balanced muscle development, and contribute to a well-rounded upper body workout.', false, false),

(7, 'Elevated Pike Push Ups', 'Elevated Pike Push-Ups are a challenging variation of the traditional push-up that specifically targets the shoulders, triceps, and upper chest. In this exercise, you start in a pike position with your hips raised and hands on an elevated surface, such as a box or bench. As you lower your upper body towards the elevated surface and push back up, the emphasis is on the shoulders, providing an effective workout for building shoulder strength and definition. Elevated Pike Push-Ups are an excellent addition to your routine for individuals looking to enhance shoulder stability, increase upper body strength, and add diversity to their push-up variations.', false, false),
(8, 'Shoulder Blade Squeeze', 'The Shoulder Blade Squeeze is a simple yet effective exercise designed to target the muscles between the shoulder blades, known as the rhomboids. To perform this exercise, you start in a seated or standing position with your back straight. Slowly retract your shoulder blades by squeezing them together, focusing on the muscles between your spine and shoulder blades. Hold the squeeze for a moment before releasing. This exercise helps improve posture, strengthens the upper back, and reduces the risk of shoulder and neck discomfort associated with poor posture. Incorporate Shoulder Blade Squeezes into your routine for a quick and beneficial way to enhance back strength and promote better shoulder alignment.', false, false),
(9, 'Shoulder Circle', 'The Shoulder Circle exercise is a simple yet effective movement that involves rotating the shoulders in circular motions. To perform this exercise, stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and relax your arms by your sides. Slowly lift your shoulders in a circular motion, moving them forward and then upward, then back and downward in a smooth, controlled manner. Reverse the direction to complete the circular movement. Shoulder Circles help increase shoulder mobility, reduce stiffness, and improve overall flexibility in the shoulder joints. This exercise is excellent for warming up the shoulders before a workout or for relieving tension and promoting better range of motion during a stretching routine.', false, false),
(10, 'Neck Rotation', 'The Neck Rotation exercise is a gentle movement designed to improve flexibility and alleviate tension in the neck muscles. To perform this exercise, sit or stand comfortably with your spine straight. Slowly turn your head to one side, bringing your chin over your shoulder, and hold the position for a moment. Return to the center and repeat on the other side. Neck Rotations help enhance neck mobility, reduce stiffness, and promote relaxation.', false, false),

(11, 'Glute Bridge', 'The Glute Bridge is a fundamental exercise targeting the gluteal muscles and the lower back. To perform this exercise, lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. Press through your heels, engaging your glutes and lifting your hips toward the ceiling. Hold the bridge position for a moment, emphasizing a straight line from your shoulders to your knees. Glute Bridges are excellent for building strength in the glutes, hamstrings, and lower back, enhancing overall lower body stability. This exercise also helps improve core strength and is a valuable addition to workouts focused on toning the posterior chain and promoting hip mobility.', false, false),
(12, 'Side Lunges', 'Side Lunges are a dynamic lower body exercise that targets the inner and outer thighs, hamstrings, and glutes. To perform this exercise, stand with your feet together and take a step to the side, bending one knee while keeping the other leg straight. Lower your body toward the bent knee, keeping your back straight and chest lifted. Push off the bent leg to return to the starting position and repeat on the other side. Side Lunges help improve lateral strength, enhance hip flexibility, and contribute to a well-rounded lower body workout.', false, false),
(13, 'Squats', 'Squats are a fundamental and effective lower body exercise that engages multiple muscle groups simultaneously. To perform a squat, stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, lower your hips back and down as if sitting into a chair, and then return to the starting position by pushing through your heels. This exercise primarily targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes, while also engaging the core and lower back for stability. Squats are renowned for their ability to build strength, improve overall lower body muscle tone, and enhance functional fitness. Incorporate squats into your workout routine for a versatile and powerful lower body exercise.', false, false),
(14, 'Assisted Pistol Squats', 'Assisted Pistol Squats are a modified version of the challenging pistol squat, providing support as you work on mastering this advanced lower body exercise. To perform this movement, hold onto a sturdy object or use a support, such as a suspension trainer or door frame. Lift one leg in front of you and slowly lower your body on the supporting leg, maintaining balance. Then, push through the heel of the supporting leg to return to the starting position. Assisted Pistol Squats help develop strength, stability, and mobility in the legs, targeting the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. This exercise is an excellent progression toward mastering the full pistol squat and offers a controlled approach for individuals working on their lower body strength and balance.', false, false),
(15, 'Forward Lunges', 'Forward Lunges are a dynamic lower body exercise that effectively targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. To perform a forward lunge, start by standing with your feet together. Take a step forward with one foot, lowering your hips until both knees are bent at a 90-degree angle. Ensure your front knee is directly above your ankle and your back knee hovers just above the ground. Push through the front heel to return to the starting position and repeat on the other leg. Forward lunges help improve lower body strength, stability, and balance, making them an essential addition to any leg workout routine.', false, false),
(16, 'Calves Exercises', 'Calf Exercises encompass various movements targeting the muscles of the calf, primarily the gastrocnemius and soleus. Common exercises include Standing Calf Raises, where you lift your heels off the ground, and Seated Calf Raises, performed while seated. These exercises involve lifting the heels against resistance to strengthen and tone the calves. Calf exercises contribute to improved ankle stability, enhanced athletic performance, and overall lower leg aesthetics. Incorporate these exercises into your routine to promote calf strength, endurance, and flexibility, ensuring a well-rounded lower body workout.', false, false),
(17, 'Knees Rotation', 'Knee Rotation is a dynamic exercise that improves knee mobility and flexibility. Start by standing with your legs close together and placing your hands on your knees. Gently rotate your knees in a clockwise and counterclockwise circular motion while maintaining light pressure with your hands on your knee. This variation adds stability and support to the exercise by engaging the muscles around the knee joint and helping to increase range of motion. Knee Rotations with your hands on your knees are a great choice for warming up or as part of a lower body flexibility routine, providing a controlled approach to improving knee health.', false, false),

(18, 'Normal Push Ups', 'Normal Push-Ups are a fundamental and effective upper body exercise that targets the chest, shoulders, triceps, and core muscles. To perform a standard push-up, start in a plank position with hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Lower your body by bending your elbows until your chest nearly touches the ground, and then push back up to the starting position. Normal Push-Ups are versatile and can be adapted to various fitness levels. They are an excellent bodyweight exercise for building upper body strength, muscle endurance, and promoting overall functional fitness. Incorporate normal push-ups into your routine for a well-rounded upper body workout.', false, false),

(19, 'Legs Down Hold', 'Legs Down Hold is an isometric core exercise that targets the lower abdominal muscles. To perform this exercise, lie on your back with your legs slightly raised from the ground. Keep your lower back pressed into the floor and lift your shoulders off the ground. Hold your legs in this position, creating a right angle with your torso. This static position engages the lower abs, helping to improve core strength and stability. Legs Down Hold is a challenging but effective exercise for toning and strengthening the lower abdominal muscles. Incorporate it into your core workout routine to enhance overall abdominal strength and definition.', false, false),
(20, 'Leg Flutters', 'Leg Flutters are a dynamic core exercise that targets the lower abdominal muscles. To perform Leg Flutters, lie on your back with your legs extended straight up toward the ceiling. Lift your shoulders off the ground, engage your core, and lower one leg towards the floor while raising the other leg. Alternate the leg movements in a fluttering motion. This exercise challenges the lower abs and helps improve core strength and endurance. Leg Flutters are an effective addition to a comprehensive core workout routine, aiding in toning and sculpting the abdominal muscles. Ensure controlled movements to maximize the benefits while minimizing strain.', false, false),
(21, 'Leg Raise', 'Leg Raises are a classic and effective core exercise that primarily targets the lower abdominal muscles. To perform Leg Raises, lie on your back with your legs straight and your arms by your sides, raise your head and do not lower it throughout the entire exercise. Lift your legs upward toward the ceiling while keeping them straight, then lower them back down without letting your feet touch the ground. This controlled movement engages the lower abs, helping to strengthen and tone the core. Leg Raises are an excellent addition to any core workout routine, promoting better abdominal definition and overall core stability. Focus on maintaining proper form to maximize the effectiveness of this simple yet powerful exercise.', false, false),
(22, 'Lay Hip Raise', 'The Lying Hip Raise is a lower body exercise that primarily targets the core muscles and glutes.To perform this exercise, lie on your back with your legs slightly raised from the ground. Begin to bend your knees to your chest, then lift your hip off the ground, then smoothly lower to the starting position. The Lying Hip Raise for Abs is an effective exercise for building core strength, improving stability, and toning both the lower abs and glutes. Incorporate it into your routine for a well-rounded core workout.', false, false),
(23, 'Twists', 'Twists are exercises designed to engage the muscles of the core, particularly the obliques. To perform twists, lie on your back with your legs slightly raised from the ground. Rotate your upper body to one side, bringing your shoulders and chest in the direction of the twist while keeping your hips stable. Return to the center and repeat on the other side. Twists help improve spinal mobility, enhance core strength, and target the muscles responsible for torso rotation. They are versatile and can be incorporated into warm-up routines or as part of a comprehensive core workout for increased flexibility and stability.', false, false),
(24, 'Crunches', 'Crunches are an engaging variation of traditional crunches that target the entire core, including the obliques and lower abdominals. To perform Crunches, spread your legs shoulder-width apart, arms to the sides, making a star shape. Begin to lift your body and right arm at the same time as your left leg and touch your ankle at the top. Do the same with your left arm and right leg. This exercise effectively engages multiple muscle groups, promoting overall core strength and definition. Star Crunches add variety to your abdominal workout routine and are particularly effective for those seeking a challenging exercise to tone and sculpt the entire midsection.', false, false),
(25, 'Bicycle Twists', 'Bicycle Twists are a dynamic core exercise that targets the entire abdominal region, including the obliques. To perform Bicycle Twists, lie on your back with your hands behind your head and legs lifted off the ground. Bring one knee towards your chest while simultaneously twisting your upper body, aiming to touch the opposite elbow to the bent knee. Alternate the movements in a pedaling motion, creating a bicycle-like action. This exercise engages the core muscles effectively, enhancing both strength and flexibility. Bicycle Twists are beneficial for toning the midsection, improving coordination, and adding a dynamic element to your core workout routine.', false, false),
(26, 'Mountain Climbers', 'Mountain Climbers are a dynamic and cardiovascular exercise that targets the core, shoulders, and hip flexors. To perform Mountain Climbers, start in a plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders. Bring one knee towards your chest and then quickly switch legs, simulating a running motion while maintaining the plank position. The continuous movement engages the core and elevates your heart rate, making it an effective full-body workout. Mountain Climbers are versatile and can be incorporated into high-intensity interval training routines or used as a dynamic warm-up exercise to enhance core strength, improve endurance, and burn calories.', false, false),
(27, 'Plank Hold', 'The Plank Hold is a foundational isometric exercise that targets the entire core, shoulders, and lower back. To perform a Plank Hold, start in a plank position with your hands directly beneath your shoulders and your body in a straight line from head to heels. Engage your core muscles and hold the position, keeping your body parallel to the ground. Plank Holds are effective for building core strength, stability, and endurance. They also engage the muscles of the arms and legs, making it a comprehensive full-body exercise. Include Plank Holds in your routine to enhance core stability, improve posture, and promote overall body strength.', false, false);

